  "__comment": "Greek/Phoenician MERCHANTMAN -- the 'round ship' (gaulos/holkas). Proportioned off the KYRENIA wreck (4th c. BC, best-preserved Greek merchant hull): 14 m long, 4.4 m beam = a 3.2:1 ratio, against the trireme's 6.2:1. That ratio IS the animal -- a trireme is a needle, this is a tub. Deep-bellied, NO RAM (the visual tell of a trader vs a warship), a single mast with a big square sail, curved sternpost, and quarter-rudders instead of a stern rudder. Cargo lashed on deck. Vanilla block textures only.",
